If the first development of the week was about who decides, the second was about who belongs. Immigration and citizenship policy hardened into something closer to an ethnonational, quasi\uc0\u8209 militarized regime. The administration invoked the Alien Enemies Act\'97an 18th\u8209 century wartime statute\'97to detain and deport migrants from Venezuela and other countries as alleged security threats. Deportations were routed through opaque arrangements with third countries like El Salvador, where some deportees disappeared or were imprisoned. Plans advanced to build a large migrant detention facility at Guant\'e1namo Bay, placing tens of thousands of people offshore, far from ordinary courts and oversight.\
