Alongside these enforcement practices, the legal architecture of citizenship itself was reworked. Trump signed executive orders attempting to end or limit birthright citizenship for children of certain non\uc0\u8209 citizens, challenging a century\u8209 old understanding of the Fourteenth Amendment. The refugee resettlement program was frozen, with admissions limited to case\u8209 by\u8209 case \'93national interest\'94 exceptions. A broad directive ended unspecified federal benefits for undocumented immigrants, threatening access to essential services. English was declared the official language of the United States, and language rules for commercial drivers were tightened, raising barriers for non\u8209 English speakers to work and interact with the state.\
